Messages:
  - To add a new page to the dashboard in this project, you need to follow three main steps: register the route, add the sidebar/navigation link, and create the page component.

### 1. Register the Route in `App.tsx`
Routes are managed using the `wouter` library. You must lazy-load your component and add a `<Route>` entry within the `AppRoutes` component, wrapping it in the `<AppRoute>` (which provides the `AppShell` layout).

**File:** `apps/web/src/App.tsx`
```tsx
// 1. Lazy load the new page
const NewPage = lazy(() => import("@/pages/app/NewPage"));

// 2. Add to AppRoutes component
function AppRoutes() {
  return (
    <Switch>
      {/* ... existing routes ... */}
      <Route path="/app/new-page">
        {() => <AppRoute><NewPage /></AppRoute>}
      </Route>
    </Switch>
  );
}
```

### 2. Add Sidebar/Navigation Items in `AppShell.tsx`
Navigation links are grouped into constants and then rendered in the sidebar. You also need to add metadata (title/subtitle) for the header.

**File:** `apps/web/src/components/AppShell.tsx`
```tsx
// 1. Add to a navigation group (e.g., businessNav)
const businessNav = [
  // ... existing items
  { to: "/app/new-page", label: "New Page Name", icon: "ti-star" },
] as const;

// 2. Add Header Metadata
const titles: Record<string, { title: string; subtitle: string }> = {
  "/app/new-page": { 
    title: "New Page Title", 
    subtitle: "Description that appears in the header" 
  },
};
```

### 3. Dashboard Page Component Structure
Dashboard pages typically follow a specific pattern: they use Tailwind CSS for layout, Tabler Icons (`ti-` classes), and `react-query` for data fetching.

**Example Structure (`apps/web/src/pages/app/NewPage.tsx`):**
```tsx
import { useQuery } from "@tanstack/react-query";

export default function NewPage() {
  // Optional: Fetch data from the API
  const { data } = useQuery({
    queryKey: ["new-page-data"],
    queryFn: () => fetch("/api/new-data").then(res => res.json())
  });

  return (
    <section className="overflow-y-auto h-full p-6 space-y-8">
      {/* Header / Section Header */}
      <div>
        <h2 className="text-xl font-bold text-[#031E43]">Section Title</h2>
        <p className="text-sm text-[#3B506D]">Supporting description</p>
      </div>

      {/* Grid of Cards (KPIs) */}
      <div className="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
        <div className="bg-white border border-[#DDDFE2] p-5 rounded-2xl shadow-sm">
          <span className="text-[10px] font-bold uppercase text-[#3B506D]">Metric</span>
          <div className="text-2xl font-extrabold text-[#031E43]">1,234</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      {/* Main Content Area (e.g., Table or List) */}
      <div className="bg-white border border-[#DDDFE2] rounded-2xl overflow-hidden shadow-sm">
        <div className="p-5 border-b border-[#DDDFE2]">
          <h3 className="text-sm font-bold">Details Table</h3>
        </div>
        <div className="p-5">
           {/* Component Content */}
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  );
}
```

### Key Files Summary:
- **Routing:** `apps/web/src/App.tsx` (Lines 14-52 for imports, 94-214 for route definitions).
- **Navigation:** `apps/web/src/components/AppShell.tsx` (Lines 54-90 for groups, 92-131 for header metadata, 204-314 for sidebar rendering).
- **Page Implementation:** `apps/web/src/pages/app/Overview.tsx` serves as the primary reference for dashboard layout patterns (KPI cards, charts, and data tables).

